FBIS4-13922 "drnes079_n_94008" FBIS-NES-94-079 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 LEBANON Governors Discuss Ban on Demonstrations Governors Discuss Ban on Demonstrations NC2304170794 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 23 Apr 94 NC2304170794 Beirut Radio Lebanon Arabic BFN [Text] The governors of Mount Lebanon, Northern Lebanon, and Southern Lebanon today chaired meetings of the local security councils to discuss the measures adopted by the Central Security Council to confront any disturbance of security following the General Labor Federation's call for demonstrations on Tuesday [26 April] despite the government's ban on demonstrations. Meanwhile, the National Defense Ministry today reminded the citizens of the decision issued by National Defense Minister Muhsin Dalull yesterday suspending arms licenses throughout Lebanon for 38 hours from Monday [25 April] evening to Wednesday [27 April] morning. The army command was ordered to implement this decision.
